## 5. Model Provider Assessment

### 5.1 Foundation Model Assessment

For each AI model provider (e.g., OpenAI, Google, Anthropic, Meta), assess the following:

| Assessment Area | Questions to Address | Vendor Response |
|----------------|---------------------|----------------|
| Training data sources | What data was the model trained on? Does it include Australian personal information? | |
| Training data consent | Was consent obtained for personal information in training data? | |
| Copyright and IP | Does the vendor provide IP indemnification for model outputs? | |
| Bias and fairness testing | Has the model been tested for bias? Are results published? | |
| Explainability | Can the model provide explanations for its outputs? | |
| Safety testing | Has the model undergone red-teaming or safety evaluation? | |
| Model card availability | Does the vendor publish a model card disclosing capabilities and limitations? | |
| Data retention | Does the vendor retain prompts or outputs? For how long? | |
| Training opt-out | Can {{ business_name }} opt out of its data being used for model training? | |

{% if bias_testing_conducted %}
{{ business_name }} has conducted bias testing. Cross-reference {{ business_name }}'s bias testing results with the vendor's bias testing disclosures to identify gaps.
{% else %}
**Recommendation:** {{ business_name }} should conduct independent bias testing for AI models used in high-risk decision-making contexts, regardless of vendor-provided testing results.
{% endif %}

