## 6. Data Flow Diagrams

### 6.1 Documentation Requirements

For each AI tool in the vendor inventory, document data flows covering: data source, {{ business_name }} system, AI vendor API/platform, and sub-processors. For each stage, record data type, classification, encryption method, processing location, and retention period.

### 6.2 Data Flow Checklist

For each documented data flow, verify:

- [ ] All data types are identified and classified
- [ ] All processing locations are documented (including sub-processor locations)
- [ ] Encryption is applied in transit and at rest at every stage
- [ ] Retention periods are defined for each stage of the data flow
- [ ] Data deletion procedures are documented for each stage
- [ ] Cross-border transfers are identified and APP 8 assessments completed

{% if data_overseas_mapped %}
{{ business_name }} has mapped overseas data flows. Incorporate AI-specific data flows into the existing overseas data flow mapping.
{% else %}
**Action required:** {{ business_name }} has not mapped overseas data flows. As a priority, document all AI-related cross-border data transfers to comply with APP 8.
{% endif %}

