## 7. Annual Audit Checklist

Conduct the following audit annually for all AI vendors classified as Critical or High risk. Medium-risk vendors should be audited biennially.

### 7.1 Contractual and Security Compliance

- [ ] DPA is current and has not been amended without {{ business_name }}'s consent
- [ ] Sub-processor list is current — no unauthorised sub-processors added
- [ ] Model training opt-out remains in effect
- [ ] Incident notification obligations are current (within 72 hours)
- [ ] Data deletion and portability terms confirmed; IP ownership terms unchanged
- [ ] Security certification (SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27001, IRAP) is current
- [ ] Annual penetration test report reviewed — no critical findings unresolved
- [ ] Vendor has not experienced an undisclosed data breach since the last audit
- [ ] Access controls reviewed — RBAC, MFA, and SSO remain in place

### 7.3 Privacy and AI-Specific Controls

- [ ] Vendor privacy policy reviewed — no adverse changes
- [ ] Data processing locations have not changed without notification
- [ ] Data retention periods have not been extended without consent
- [ ] Model version in use is documented and current
- [ ] Bias testing results reviewed (if applicable to use case)
- [ ] Output accuracy benchmarks reviewed — no significant degradation
- [ ] Human override capability confirmed as operational
- [ ] AI-specific incident response procedures tested

{% if vendor_audit_rights %}
{{ business_name }} has audit rights with its AI vendors. Exercise these rights at least annually for Critical vendors and biennially for High-risk vendors.
{% else %}
**Action required:** {{ business_name }} does not have contractual audit rights with AI vendors. Negotiate audit rights into existing and future vendor agreements. Where vendors refuse audit rights, request SOC 2 Type II reports or equivalent independent assurance.
{% endif %}

