## 8. Risk Scoring Matrix

Score each AI vendor on the following dimensions (1 = Low to 5 = Critical):

| Dimension | 1 (Low) | 3 (Medium) | 5 (Critical) | Score |
|-----------|---------|------------|---------------|-------|
| Data sensitivity | Public data only | Internal data | Restricted / sensitive PI | |
| Data volume | Minimal | Moderate | Large-scale PI processing | |
| Cross-border transfers | Australia only | Adequate-protection jurisdiction | No data protection framework | |
| Business dependency | Nice-to-have | Supports key process | Core to operations | |
| Vendor maturity | Enterprise, established | Mid-market | Startup, unproven | |
| Security posture | SOC 2 + ISO 27001 | SOC 2 only | No certification | |
| Incident history | No breaches | Minor incidents | Major breach in last 3 years | |
| AI-specific risks | Low autonomy, human-reviewed | Moderate autonomy | Fully automated decisions | |

**Total score interpretation:**

| Score Range | Risk Level | Review Frequency | Escalation |
|-------------|-----------|-----------------|------------|
| 8-16 | Low | Annually | Standard review |
| 17-24 | Medium | Six-monthly | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} |
| 25-32 | High | Quarterly | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} + senior leadership |
| 33-40 | Critical | Monthly | Senior leadership + legal review |

