## 9. Incident Notification Chain

### 9.1 Vendor Incident Notification Requirements

All AI vendor contracts must require notification to {{ business_name }} in the following scenarios:

| Incident Type | Notification Timeframe | Notify |
|---------------|----------------------|--------|
| Data breach involving {{ business_name }}'s data | Within 72 hours | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} |
| Unauthorised sub-processor access or model compromise | Within 48 hours | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} + IT security |
| Service outage affecting data integrity | Within 24 hours | IT operations |
| Change in data processing location or sub-processors | 30 days advance notice | {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} |
| Regulatory action against vendor | Within 5 business days | Legal + {{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} |

### 9.2 {{ business_name }} Internal Escalation

1. Receive vendor notification and log in incident register ({{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }})
2. Assess severity and determine if NDB scheme reporting is required ({{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} + legal)
3. If eligible data breach — notify OAIC within 30 days or as soon as practicable (senior leadership)
4. Notify affected individuals if required under the NDB scheme (senior leadership)
5. Conduct root cause analysis with the vendor ({{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }} + IT security)
6. Update risk score and review vendor classification ({{ ai_governance_contact if ai_governance_contact else "AI governance contact" }})

{% if ndb_ai_process %}
{{ business_name }} has an NDB process that covers AI-related incidents. Ensure this process is tested annually with a tabletop exercise involving an AI vendor breach scenario.
{% else %}
**Action required:** {{ business_name }} should ensure its Notifiable Data Breaches process explicitly covers incidents originating from AI vendors and sub-processors. The OAIC provides NDB guidance at [www.oaic.gov.au](https://www.oaic.gov.au).
{% endif %}

{% if ai_incident_register %}
{{ business_name }} maintains an AI incident register. All vendor-reported incidents must be recorded in this register within 24 hours of receipt.
{% else %}
**Recommendation:** {{ business_name }} should establish an AI incident register to track vendor-reported incidents alongside internally detected AI incidents.
{% endif %}

